# Goalify Frontend — Artistic Direction

**Afin que** toute modification ou suggestion sur le frontend respecte l’identité visuelle de l’application, garde toujours en contexte la direction artistique ci‑dessous, quel que soit la demande.

---

## 1. Intent

- **Calm, intelligent, softly elegant** mobile-first interface for a personal life-tracking app (goals, habits, activities) — a “personal cockpit”.
- The app **supports the user quietly, without pressure**. Visual identity must feel **clear, structured, reassuring**, never aggressive or gamified.

---

## 2. Style principles

- **Soft minimalism, warm and human**
- **Strong visual hierarchy** with generous spacing
- **Subtle personality through details**, not decoration
- **No gamification, no emojis, no flashy elements**

---

## 3. Layout & UI

- **Card-based layout** with soft rounded corners (`rounded-xl`, `rounded-2xl`)
- Strict separation between life domains (goals, habits, media, health)
- Dashboard acts as a **cockpit**: overview first, details second
- Prefer **smooth, slow micro-interactions** (e.g. `duration-200`, `duration-300`)

---

## 4. Color palette (Tailwind @theme in `src/styles.css`)

Use **only** these semantic tokens. No raw grays or bright primaries.

| Token | Usage |
|-------|--------|
| `surface` | Main background (honey cream) |
| `surface-alt` | Cards, header, sidebar, inputs background |
| `border` | Borders |
| `muted` | Secondary text, placeholders |
| `ink` / `ink-strong` | Body and heading text |
| `sage` / `sage-soft` | Focus rings, accents, priority/category |
| `lilac` / `lilac-soft` | Nav active, filter pills, soft accents |
| `peach` / `peach-soft` | Primary CTAs, FAB, key actions |
| `blush` | Avatar, soft highlights |
| `rose` | High-priority badge |
| `accent` / `accent-soft` | Alias for peach (buttons) |

- **Background never pure white** — use `surface` or `surface-alt`.
- **Maximum two accent colors per screen** (e.g. peach + lilac, or sage + peach).

---

## 5. Shadows

- Use **warm-tinted shadows**: classes `shadow-warm` and `shadow-warm-md` (defined in `styles.css`), not generic `shadow-sm`/`shadow-md`.
- Keeps the overall feel warm and cohesive.

---

## 6. Typography

- **Font**: Inter (already loaded in `index.html`).
- **High legibility**: slightly expressive titles (`font-semibold`, `tracking-tight`), neutral body text.
- Prefer `text-ink` / `text-ink-strong` for text, `text-muted` for secondary.

---

## 7. Mood & feeling

- **Calm, clarity, intelligence** — “Everything is under control”
- **Elegant, thoughtful, mature**
- References (vibe, not copy): Notion (clarity), GitHub (progress), Apple Health (calm), Letterboxd (tasteful organization)

---

## 8. Conventions when changing UI

- **No logic change** unless explicitly requested: prefer HTML + Tailwind only for visual tweaks.
- **Do not move** main structure (e.g. sidebar, header, main) unless asked.
- **New components / pages**: use the same palette (`surface`, `surface-alt`, `border`, `peach`, `lilac-soft`, etc.), same rounded corners, same shadow utilities (`shadow-warm`, `shadow-warm-md`).
- **Buttons**: primary = `bg-peach` / `hover:bg-peach-soft`; secondary = bordered with `border-border` and `hover:bg-surface-alt` or `hover:bg-peach-soft/40`.
- **Forms**: inputs with `rounded-xl`, `border-border`, `bg-surface`, focus `focus:ring-sage-soft` / `focus:border-sage-soft`.

When answering or implementing any frontend request, apply this artistic direction by default so the app stays consistent and on-brand.
